The paper deals with term rewriting systems, which are a topic in theoretical computer science and logic (cs.LO). The focus is on applicative term rewriting systems, which are a subclass of term rewriting systems that are closely related to functional programming (cs.PL). The paper also discusses termination and complexity, which are topics in theoretical computer science and algorithms (cs.TC). The paper uses mathematical proofs and counterexamples, which are common in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses non-termination, which is a topic in automata theory and formal languages (cs.FL).
